text: What a disappointment. Well Pierce still does have it as a spy and it looks like Olga got to play with another Bond. However, his role in this movie though was quite unnerving. He starts off as an agent trying to get the bad guy while encountering his former protege who has been assigned to kill him but then turns kind of psychotic as he "teaches" his former protege another lesson as he is still bitter about a mistake made on job years ago. The plot was convoluted and took me in and out of the story almost throughout the movie. I spent more time trying to understand the movie than actually enjoying it. So many twists and elements that just don't need to be for an espionage, action flick. I hate to say it but this was pretty poor overall. A disappointment for those who like myself expected this to be good.
